                            <comment id="122725" author="olivergierke" created="Tue, 29 Dec 2015 08:09:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What&apos;s the reason you&apos;re using Spring Data JPA 1.9.0? Boot ships with 1.9.1 out of the box which transitively includes Spring Data Commons 1.11.1, which in turn had &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATACMNS-761&quot; title=&quot;PageableHandlerMethodArgumentResolver reduces page size by one if on-indexed parameters are used&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DATACMNS-761&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DATACMNS-761&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fixed. So unless you can come up with a test case against 1.9.1, I think we&apos;ll just close this as duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATACMNS-761&quot; title=&quot;PageableHandlerMethodArgumentResolver reduces page size by one if on-indexed parameters are used&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DATACMNS-761&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DATACMNS-761&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="122727" author="smallufo" created="Tue, 29 Dec 2015 10:32:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well , it seems my subject depends on spring-data-jpa 1.9.0 .&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After upgrading to 1.9.2 (which depends on spring-data-commons:jar:1.11.2) , it solves. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="122728" author="olivergierke" created="Tue, 29 Dec 2015 10:42:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s great news! Generally speaking: the Boot releases usually point to the latest and greatest fixes, so unless you have very special reasons it&apos;s best to rely on the Spring Data version Boot ships out of the box. That was you automatically benefit from updates and fixes in downstream dependencies.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
